																		Thanks, Attribution and Other Matters
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225880" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1449367637 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Dec 2015 02:07</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2418158">
									

<p>Firstly, thanks to reviewers such as augmentedspartan and psul.</p>
<p>Secondly, the image used is from Wikipedia (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immersion_(virtual_reality)#/media/File:AC89-0437-20_a.jpegunder">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immersion_(virtual_reality)#/media/File:AC89-0437-20_a.jpegunder</a>) under Public Domain.</p>
<p>SCPs featured include: SCP-990 (Dream Man) by Dave Rapp</p>
<p>Thirdly, this Tale is part of the &quot;series&quot; that is in canon with <a href="/how-173-got-to-site-19">How 173 Got to Site-19</a>. The Foundation on the mutliversal scale, as a literal foundation over all realities. This also doubles as a re-imagining of SCP-990 and the Oneiroi Collective.</p>

							</div>

								
